A Chama Cha Mashinani rally planned for today for the launch of Governor Isaac Rutto&rsquo;s (pictured) campaign has been postponed for the third time.Sources say it was cancelled due to NASA presidential candidate Raila Odinga&rsquo;s tight schedule. He was expected to make an appearance.The party will instead hold a meeting in Bomet Stadium to name its aspirants who won in last week&rsquo;s primaries, it said in a statement.&ldquo;The governor will use the occasion to address issues, including devolution milestones and bottlenecks and also explain to the electorate why NASA is a better option compared to Jubilee,&rdquo; the statements says.